13:02.550 --> 13:05.252
I don't know, Madison, but
I'm okay with us going out.
Are you?

13:05.286 --> 13:06.353
Sure.

13:06.387 --> 13:07.554
Then let's do it.

13:07.588 --> 13:08.555
I'll call you tonight.

13:08.589 --> 13:09.923
All right.

13:11.125 --> 13:12.893
Hey, I was looking for you.

13:12.927 --> 13:14.227
I don't have
majorette practice,

13:14.262 --> 13:15.929
so you want to go
somewhere and hang out?

13:15.963 --> 13:18.265
I can't. I have a
huge test tomorrow.

13:18.299 --> 13:19.366
You want to study at my house?

13:19.400 --> 13:20.567
It's my English lit test.

13:20.601 --> 13:22.035
It's a take-home.
I turn it in tomorrow.

13:22.070 --> 13:26.573
Just that? Well, I wanted
to ask you about something.

13:26.607 --> 13:29.976
Oh. I already know about Jack
and Madison. They're going
out.

13:30.011 --> 13:31.578
They're going out?

13:31.612 --> 13:34.247
Like, out out? Dating?

13:34.282 --> 13:36.416
Yeah. But we're all still
going to be friends.

13:36.451 --> 13:37.784
Why? Why not?

13:37.819 --> 13:38.985
He's your boyfriend.

13:39.020 --> 13:40.420
Not anymore.

13:40.455 --> 13:42.923
Yeah, well, I wish I
could be like you.

13:42.957 --> 13:44.257
I wish Ricky could
see other women

13:44.292 --> 13:46.059
and I could just accept that,
but I can't.

13:46.094 --> 13:47.227
Ricky's seeing someone?

13:47.261 --> 13:48.595
He slept with someone.

13:48.629 --> 13:49.963
You know that girl named Zoe?

13:49.997 --> 13:51.932
Sorry.

13:51.966 --> 13:53.533
Who'd you sleep with?
Her boyfriend?

13:53.568 --> 13:55.602
That was a long time ago.

13:55.636 --> 13:56.937
That was months ago.

13:56.971 --> 13:58.939
Ricky and I aren't what
we were months ago.

13:58.973 --> 14:02.209
That's why when Zoe called me
and told me she slept with
him,

14:02.243 --> 14:03.877
I got really upset,

14:03.911 --> 14:07.047
and I drove over to
the butcher shop,

14:07.081 --> 14:09.149
and I threw my phone
at his window.

14:09.183 --> 14:11.718
Only I missed,

14:11.753 --> 14:14.387
and I hit the bigger
window at the butcher shop,

14:14.422 --> 14:17.390
so now I owe...

14:18.392 --> 14:19.626
Wow.

14:19.660 --> 14:21.828
Yeah. Where am I going to
get that kind of money?

14:21.863 --> 14:23.563
I don't know.

14:23.598 --> 14:25.298
It costs this
much for a window?

14:25.333 --> 14:26.600
Yeah, and the thing is

14:26.634 --> 14:28.902
Ricky gives all his money
to Amy and that stupid baby,

14:28.936 --> 14:30.570
so I have to come
up with this today,

14:30.605 --> 14:32.773
or he's going to go to my
dad and ask him for it.

14:32.807 --> 14:34.474
Then you should go
to your father first.

14:34.509 --> 14:37.911
Yeah. Or...

14:37.945 --> 14:39.446
Maybe you could loan it to me?

14:40.648 --> 14:42.749
I mean, if you don't want to,

14:42.784 --> 14:45.252
or if it puts you in
an awkward position--

14:45.286 --> 14:47.587
I mean, if I had the
money and you came to me

14:47.622 --> 14:50.190
and asked me for the loan,
of course I would, but--

14:50.224 --> 14:53.593
I can't. I'm sorry.

14:53.628 --> 14:54.828
Good luck.

15:01.235 --> 15:02.536
Got some money for me?

15:02.570 --> 15:04.104
No, I don't.

15:04.138 --> 15:05.539
Bunny, here's the thing--

15:05.573 --> 15:07.874
Adrian doesn't have any money,

15:07.909 --> 15:09.543
and I could probably
get the money

15:09.577 --> 15:12.212
if I went to Adrian's dad
and told him what happened.

15:12.246 --> 15:14.548
But when I started
thinking about it,

15:14.582 --> 15:16.116
it's not entirely her fault.

15:16.150 --> 15:17.384
I did the wrong thing,

15:17.418 --> 15:19.052
and now I'd like to
do the right thing

15:19.086 --> 15:20.287
and pay for that window.

15:20.321 --> 15:21.888
I shouldn't have
cheated on Adrian,

15:21.923 --> 15:23.557
and I pushed her to the limit.

15:23.591 --> 15:28.228
She's been trying really hard,
and I haven't.

15:28.262 --> 15:30.130
I want to figure out
some way to pay you.

15:30.164 --> 15:31.898
<i>Look, chupacabra,</i>

15:31.933 --> 15:34.234
there's no excuse for
Adrian breaking a window,

15:34.268 --> 15:36.369
so don't try to make
excuses for her.

15:36.404 --> 15:37.904
But if you want to
pay for the window--

15:37.939 --> 15:41.241
And I don't think you're
doing her any favor by doing
that,

15:41.275 --> 15:43.743
then you go to Mr. Boykevich,
tell him what happened,

15:43.778 --> 15:45.645
and work something
out with him.

15:45.680 --> 15:48.081
And when you do,
just keep in mind

15:48.115 --> 15:49.282
that he has a right

15:49.317 --> 15:52.686
to call the police
and press charges.

15:59.427 --> 16:00.694
I tried to find
you after school.

16:00.728 --> 16:02.562
I told you I had
to be here on time.

16:02.597 --> 16:04.531
I'm sorry about that.

16:04.565 --> 16:06.199
I didn't know if I
was coming to work.

16:06.234 --> 16:07.934
I really need to go
over and talk to Amy.

16:07.969 --> 16:10.036
I thought that was over.
Maybe it is,

16:10.071 --> 16:12.205
but I don't like
the way it ended.

16:12.240 --> 16:13.707
Maybe I didn't do
the right thing.

16:13.741 --> 16:16.209
Maybe I should have broken
up with Amy before now,

16:16.244 --> 16:17.878
before Maria ever came here.

16:17.912 --> 16:20.547
Before I met Maria, even.

16:20.581 --> 16:22.549
But I don't think
that was right.

16:22.583 --> 16:24.217
I don't deserve that after
all we've been through.

16:24.252 --> 16:25.785
Why don't you just
leave it alone?

16:25.820 --> 16:27.554
Don't go talking to
Amy again right now.

16:27.588 --> 16:29.222
You'll just
humiliate yourself.

16:29.257 --> 16:32.559
You have a girlfriend. She
has a boyfriend. That's it.
It's over.

16:32.593 --> 16:34.060
Just accept it for now.

16:34.095 --> 16:36.196
I don't want it to be
over for you, believe me,

16:36.230 --> 16:38.265
but when it's over, it's over.

16:40.268 --> 16:41.735
You and Adrian,
you guys working things out?

16:41.769 --> 16:44.404
She threw her cell phone
through that window last
night,

16:44.438 --> 16:46.239
trying to break my window.

16:46.274 --> 16:48.575
And now she should pay for it,
but she can't,

16:48.609 --> 16:50.076
so I'm going to have to.

16:50.111 --> 16:52.412
So I'm going to see your
father and tell him what
happened,

16:52.446 --> 16:54.314
and ask him if I can
pay for it over time.

16:54.348 --> 16:55.815
But Adrian broke the window.

16:55.850 --> 16:58.251
It's my fault.
It's my responsibility.

16:58.286 --> 17:00.287
I just hate
disappointing your dad.

17:00.321 --> 17:03.857
Yeah. I know how that is.

17:03.891 --> 17:04.991
How much was the window?

17:22.076 --> 17:23.676
You have that
much money on you?

17:24.878 --> 17:26.212
I wasn't asking you for money.

17:26.247 --> 17:27.881
I can't take this.

17:27.915 --> 17:29.482
I want to take it,
but I can't.

17:29.517 --> 17:31.518
Go ahead. It's not a loan.
You can have it.

17:31.552 --> 17:33.186
No. I don't want your money.

17:33.220 --> 17:37.190
I mean, I want it,
but there's n.

17:37.224 --> 17:38.525
And this is about
Adrian and me.

17:38.559 --> 17:39.926
This isn't about you and me.

17:42.730 --> 17:44.531
It is about you and me.

17:44.565 --> 17:46.366
My dad wanted you and
me to work together

17:46.400 --> 17:49.202
because he wanted
us to be friends.

17:49.236 --> 17:51.171
So, from one
friend to another,

17:51.205 --> 17:53.173
take it. Otherwise,
you're going to be

17:53.207 --> 17:55.642
earning money that could have
been money John could have,

17:55.676 --> 17:59.546
and as a friend,
I want to confess something--

17:59.580 --> 18:01.815
The thing that's kept me
from breaking up with Amy,

18:01.849 --> 18:05.819
the real thing,
is even though I don't know

18:05.853 --> 18:09.489
if I love Amy or
if I love Maria,

18:09.523 --> 18:13.860
I do know that I
love your son.

18:13.894 --> 18:15.595
You love my son? Yup.

18:15.629 --> 18:17.998
It kills me to think I'm not
going to see him every day

18:18.032 --> 18:19.099
if I break up with Amy.

18:19.133 --> 18:20.934
You sure about
breaking up with Amy?

18:20.968 --> 18:24.170
I was sure, but Adrian keeps
trying to talk me out of it.

18:24.205 --> 18:26.673
You're not staying in the
relationship just for John.

18:26.707 --> 18:29.175
Well, maybe.

18:29.210 --> 18:30.844
Maybe we both need
legal agreements

18:30.878 --> 18:32.846
to be able to see John.

18:32.880 --> 18:35.181
Although I don't think I have
a chance in hell of getting
that one.

18:35.216 --> 18:38.051
Me, neither. I'm just doing
it because Adrian says to do
it.

18:38.085 --> 18:40.854
If neither of us were
listening to Adrian's advice
about things,

18:40.888 --> 18:42.622
what would we do?

18:48.229 --> 18:49.529
Who is it?

18:49.563 --> 18:51.231
It's me, Tom. It's Adrian.

18:54.235 --> 18:55.201
Hi, Adrian.

18:55.236 --> 18:56.536
Hi. Come in.

18:56.570 --> 18:59.706
Is Grace home?

18:59.740 --> 19:00.707
No.

19:00.741 --> 19:03.143
Oh.

19:03.177 --> 19:05.578
Um, maybe I'll wait.

19:05.613 --> 19:06.813
Yes, wait.

19:06.847 --> 19:09.482
You can wait as
long as you want.

19:09.517 --> 19:11.251
You want a soda or something?

19:11.285 --> 19:12.585
Yeah. Thanks.

19:12.620 --> 19:13.620
Come on.

19:16.690 --> 19:18.825
What can I get you?

19:18.859 --> 19:20.794
Your wish is my command.

19:20.828 --> 19:23.329
Anything you have
will be fine.

19:23.364 --> 19:24.831
Everything I have is yours.

19:24.865 --> 19:26.066
Anything?

19:26.100 --> 19:27.700
Anything.

19:27.735 --> 19:30.804
Actually, I came over to ask
Grace to reconsider giving me
a loan.

19:30.838 --> 19:33.039
I really need a loan.

19:33.074 --> 19:34.140
How much you need?

19:34.175 --> 19:36.009
I'll give you some money.

19:44.185 --> 19:45.552
Okay.

19:46.720 --> 19:49.689
Large bills or small bills?

19:49.723 --> 19:51.057
You have that kind of money?

19:51.092 --> 19:52.292
Yes, I do.

19:52.326 --> 19:54.427
You know I would never
take advantage of you.

19:54.462 --> 19:55.562
I know.

19:55.596 --> 19:57.664
But, if I don't get the money

19:57.698 --> 20:00.166
to pay Ricky for
something I did,

20:00.201 --> 20:01.501
then he's going
to tell my dad,

20:01.535 --> 20:04.170
and I could be in
a lot of trouble.

20:04.205 --> 20:06.940
And besides that, I don't
want my dad to know how
stupid I am.

20:06.974 --> 20:09.843
You don't have to
explain anything.

20:09.877 --> 20:12.312
You want the money,
I'll give you the money.

20:12.346 --> 20:14.848
It's just between you and me.

20:14.882 --> 20:17.083
No one else will ever know.
Really?

20:17.118 --> 20:19.519
Really. I love you.

20:19.553 --> 20:21.187
You know I love you.

20:21.222 --> 20:23.456
I've always loved you.

20:23.491 --> 20:24.858
Aw, Tom.

20:24.892 --> 20:26.359
I love you, too.

20:26.393 --> 20:29.028
And I'll pay you back. I
don't know when, but I will.

20:29.063 --> 20:31.731
That doesn't matter.
I want to give you the money.

20:40.221 --> 20:41.755
It's none of my business,
that's why.

20:41.790 --> 20:43.757
It's none of your business
if Ben's girlfriend

20:43.792 --> 20:44.925
shows up from Italy?

20:44.959 --> 20:46.427
I had to find out
from my best friends.

20:46.461 --> 20:48.095
Yes, you had to find
out from someone else,

20:48.129 --> 20:49.596
because whatever
happens to you and Ben

20:49.631 --> 20:50.764
should be between you and Ben,

20:50.799 --> 20:53.100
not you and Ben and me
or the whole school.

20:53.134 --> 20:55.769
I couldn't wait any longer. I
knew it was going to happen.

20:55.804 --> 20:57.304
I knew he was going
to break up with me.

20:57.339 --> 20:58.772
He knew he was going
to break up with me.

20:58.807 --> 21:00.708
I just wanted him to say it,
and he said it.

21:00.742 --> 21:03.544
We broke up, and it
is for real this time.

21:03.578 --> 21:05.379
And I am fine with that.

21:05.413 --> 21:06.747
Why are you fine with that?

21:06.781 --> 21:09.216
Because I have no choice
but to be fine with that.

21:09.250 --> 21:11.385
Because that is what it is.

21:11.419 --> 21:13.053
Ben Boykevich went
to Italy last summer

21:13.088 --> 21:14.221
and got himself a girlfriend.

21:14.255 --> 21:16.056
He met a girl.
Of course he met a girl.

21:16.091 --> 21:17.391
He probably met lots of girls.

21:17.425 --> 21:19.326
He didn't go to a
monastery in Italy.

21:19.361 --> 21:20.427
Well, he should have.

21:20.462 --> 21:21.428
But he didn't.

21:21.463 --> 21:22.529
He made a friend,

21:22.564 --> 21:23.731
a friend who really likes him,

21:23.765 --> 21:25.232
but she lives halfway
around the world,

21:25.266 --> 21:28.736
so it's not a geographically
appropriate relationship.

21:28.770 --> 21:31.405
Neither is your relationship
with this Jimmy guy.

21:31.439 --> 21:33.240
He may as well be halfway
around the world,

21:33.274 --> 21:35.075
so neither of you should
break up with each other

21:35.110 --> 21:36.243
just because you
met other people

21:36.277 --> 21:37.611
who don't live
anywhere near here.

21:37.645 --> 21:40.714
You're not moving for
this guy, are you?

21:40.749 --> 21:43.484
You and Mom aren't moving
because of her old boyfriend
and your new one.

21:43.518 --> 21:44.651
I doubt it.

21:44.686 --> 21:47.054
Jimmy is just a guy
that I flirted with

21:47.088 --> 21:50.557
in the market late at night.

21:50.592 --> 21:52.226
He's a good-looking guy,

21:52.260 --> 21:55.562
but I may have slightly
exaggerated our involvement.

21:55.597 --> 21:57.898
He asked me out for a pizza,
and Mom said I couldn't go,

21:57.932 --> 21:59.333
so he gave me his number.

21:59.367 --> 22:02.169
I never called him,
and that's about it.

22:03.371 --> 22:05.205
Yeah. Afraid so.

22:05.240 --> 22:08.008
So you're not even thinking
about moving or taking John
away?

22:08.042 --> 22:09.176
No.

22:09.210 --> 22:11.011
I don't want to move
because of a guy.

22:11.045 --> 22:14.348
I would never move John
just to be with a guy,

22:14.382 --> 22:16.016
and I want Mom to come home.

22:16.050 --> 22:20.020
Any word on that?

22:20.054 --> 22:21.655
I've said everything
I can say to her.

22:21.689 --> 22:23.023
I told her I'm sorry.

22:23.057 --> 22:25.025
I told her I love her.

22:25.059 --> 22:27.528
I told her how much I want
to keep this family together.

22:27.562 --> 22:30.531
I've said everything I can
think of to say to her. I
don't know what else to do.

22:30.565 --> 22:34.535
It's two hours away. Why
don't you drive and see
Robbie and talk to her?

22:34.569 --> 22:37.371
Because I don't feel like
driving two hours just to be
rejected.

22:37.405 --> 22:38.705
She has to want me.

22:38.740 --> 22:41.041
She has to want to fix this.
She has to say what I said,

22:41.075 --> 22:42.643
that she's sorry and loves me

22:42.677 --> 22:44.378
and she wants to keep
the family together.

22:44.412 --> 22:45.813
Until then, I don't know.

22:45.847 --> 22:47.815
Maybe she would say that
to you if she say you.

22:47.849 --> 22:49.950
I doubt it.

22:51.019 --> 22:53.053
I'll just take Moose
for a ride instead.

22:53.087 --> 22:55.389
I feel like getting out
of here for a while.

22:55.423 --> 22:56.423
I'll be back.

23:04.032 --> 23:05.866
You're right. He really
should go up there.

23:05.900 --> 23:07.434
Of course he's going up there.

23:07.469 --> 23:09.770
You don't think he's just
taking Moose for a ride, do
you?

23:09.804 --> 23:12.005
I kind of feel like
going for a ride myself.

23:12.040 --> 23:14.675
Would you watch John? I don't
think he'll wake up for a few
hours.

23:14.709 --> 23:15.776
Just listen out for him.

23:15.810 --> 23:18.545
I'll do that.

23:18.580 --> 23:19.680
Where you going?

23:19.714 --> 23:21.315
To break up with Ben again?

23:21.349 --> 23:22.850
Maybe.

23:22.884 --> 23:27.354
I don't know. I just don't
like the way we ended it.

23:27.388 --> 23:29.957
We should have had a
conversation in private, like
Ben wanted.

23:29.991 --> 23:32.693
Maybe you should go
talk to Ricky instead.

23:32.727 --> 23:36.163
What are you going to do
about Ricky and his demand
for a custody agreement?

23:36.197 --> 23:38.699
Obviously, he wants that
because he doesn't trust me,

23:38.733 --> 23:42.035
and if he doesn't trust me,
then I don't trust him.

23:42.070 --> 23:43.837
I'm not giving him
anything he wants,

23:43.872 --> 23:45.939
especially while
he's with Adrian.

23:45.974 --> 23:47.875
His girlfriend hates me,

23:47.909 --> 23:49.443
so he can demand all he wants,

23:49.477 --> 23:53.747
but I'm not giving
him or her anything.

23:56.084 --> 23:57.918
I have the money. Let me in.

24:04.025 --> 24:05.325
Where'd you get it?

24:05.360 --> 24:06.860
I got it. That's all
you need to know.

24:06.895 --> 24:09.296
From a guy? Like I had sex
with someone for money?

24:09.330 --> 24:10.297
Is that what you're implying?

24:10.331 --> 24:11.465
Where'd you get the money?

24:11.499 --> 24:12.666
That doesn't matter, does it?

24:12.700 --> 24:14.301
I thought you'd be
happy that I have it.

24:14.335 --> 24:15.969
I'm not. And why not?

24:16.004 --> 24:17.337
Because I've taken care of it.

24:17.372 --> 24:18.605
I got the money.

24:18.640 --> 24:20.674
Where'd you get the money?
From a friend.

24:20.708 --> 24:22.342
That's where I got it.
From a friend.

24:22.377 --> 24:23.577
Well, give it back.

24:23.611 --> 24:25.679
All right. I'll give it back.

24:25.713 --> 24:27.347
Where'd you get the money?

24:27.382 --> 24:28.515
I talked to Ben's dad.

24:28.550 --> 24:30.350
He's going to let me
pay it back over time.

24:30.385 --> 24:31.485
Where'd you get the money?

24:31.519 --> 24:33.020
I told my dad
what had happened,

24:33.054 --> 24:35.188
and I told him I was sorry,

24:35.223 --> 24:37.524
and I told him I'd
work around the house

24:37.559 --> 24:39.593
and do whatever I
could to pay him back.

24:39.627 --> 24:40.627
Are you lying?

24:41.896 --> 24:42.996
Are you?

24:54.075 --> 24:56.376
I'm sorry I cheated on you.

24:56.411 --> 24:58.045
I don't want to cheat
on you, Adrian.

24:58.079 --> 24:59.980
Good, because I can't take it

25:00.014 --> 25:02.616
if you cheat on me again.
I can't.

25:04.586 --> 25:09.323
It's just that Tammy's
very much in love with Tom.

25:09.357 --> 25:11.325
We had hoped that maybe,
in a few years,

25:11.359 --> 25:13.660
they could possibly
even get married.

25:13.695 --> 25:14.995
I mean, he proposed to her.

25:15.029 --> 25:17.030
At one time,
he wanted to marry her.

25:17.065 --> 25:20.500
I don't know what happened. I
didn't even know they broke
up.

25:20.535 --> 25:22.035
Tammy must be heartbroken.

25:22.070 --> 25:25.339
Do you think that it could
be a misunderstanding?

25:25.373 --> 25:27.374
It must just be a
misunderstanding.

25:28.977 --> 25:33.814
She thinks it's because she
wouldn't have sex with him.

25:35.650 --> 25:38.151
Oh, hi.

25:38.186 --> 25:40.320
Didn't realize you were
in here. How are you?

25:40.355 --> 25:42.522
Grace, Donnie and
Adele are here,

