40:08.971 --> 40:10.972
They're for Amy.
I'll save her a couple.

40:11.006 --> 40:12.173
Maybe she could come out here.

40:12.207 --> 40:13.941
You want me to tell her,
in front of Ricky,

40:13.976 --> 40:16.310
that you want her to come
out here? No, forget it.

40:16.345 --> 40:17.678
Why do you need
to talk to Amy?

40:17.713 --> 40:19.947
I want to tell her I'm
sorry about her and Ben,

40:19.982 --> 40:25.586
and I think that maybe
we should be friends.

40:26.788 --> 40:28.356
I want to be her friend.

40:28.390 --> 40:29.357
Oh, really?

40:29.391 --> 40:31.125
Really.

40:31.159 --> 40:34.095
I want to be Amy's friend.

40:34.129 --> 40:36.731
Wow. You really are
in love with Ricky.

40:38.100 --> 40:40.334
Yeah, I really am.

40:40.369 --> 40:41.736
You know what else I think?

40:41.770 --> 40:43.571
Maybe, for the first time,

40:43.605 --> 40:46.741
I really understand
that in a single moment,

40:46.775 --> 40:48.743
a person can make
one wrong decision

40:48.777 --> 40:51.746
and it can affect the
rest of their life.

40:51.780 --> 40:55.049
Amy and Ricky had sex,
and I broke a window.

40:55.083 --> 40:57.518
Yeah, well, I bet you
got more satisfaction

40:57.552 --> 40:59.153
out of your bad
decision than they did.

41:03.125 --> 41:06.427
Let me get that. I was going
to get that. He just got all
fussy.

41:06.461 --> 41:08.429
I got it.

41:08.463 --> 41:10.765
I'll help you.

41:10.799 --> 41:13.000
You don't need to stick around

41:13.035 --> 41:15.770
and pretend like you
want to help clean up.

41:15.804 --> 41:18.472
I know you want to talk. I
know you want some kind of
agreement,

41:18.507 --> 41:21.542
and I've been thinking about
that, about what you said.

41:21.576 --> 41:23.077
Yeah, I've been thinking
about that, too,

41:23.111 --> 41:25.079
and I'm soy.

41:25.113 --> 41:27.415
I'm sorry I even
brought it up.

41:27.449 --> 41:30.751
It's just that when you left
town without telling me,

41:30.786 --> 41:32.787
I got scared I was never
going to see John again.

41:32.821 --> 41:34.188
I get scared that
you'll take off

41:34.222 --> 41:35.756
and you'll never
see John again.

41:35.791 --> 41:37.191
You're interested
in seeing him now,

41:37.225 --> 41:39.026
but maybe some day,
you'll change your mind.

41:39.061 --> 41:42.697
Maybe you'll want
to move around

41:42.731 --> 41:44.398
and you won't be here
to take care of him.

41:44.433 --> 41:45.866
No, I'm not going to do that.

41:45.901 --> 41:48.035
What if you got the
chance to go to Alaska

41:48.070 --> 41:51.372
and make a million dollars,
driving on the ice roads,

41:51.406 --> 41:53.774
but you'd have to be
gone for six months?

41:53.809 --> 41:56.377
I don't like the cold.

41:56.411 --> 41:59.380
But what if you get a
scholarship to Julliard,

41:59.414 --> 42:01.716
and you take off for New York,
and you take John with you?

42:01.750 --> 42:05.052
If anything like
that ever happens,

42:05.087 --> 42:06.887
then we'll sit down and
we'll talk about it

42:06.922 --> 42:08.956
and figure out
what's best for John.

42:10.125 --> 42:11.559
And us.

42:11.593 --> 42:13.060
So you're acknowledging
that there is an us?

42:13.095 --> 42:17.064
Yeah. I guess it's
time we both realized

42:17.099 --> 42:19.066
that we are a family,

42:19.101 --> 42:21.002
even though you and
I are not a couple.

42:22.938 --> 42:24.739
So when you broke
up with Ben...

42:24.773 --> 42:28.576
I broke up with him,
or he broke up with me.

42:28.610 --> 42:31.712
We broke up with each other.

42:31.747 --> 42:33.080
It's been coming for a while.

42:33.115 --> 42:34.849
I still like him,

42:34.883 --> 42:38.686
and he's been in John's
life all this time.

42:38.720 --> 42:41.155
I still want him to see John
if he still wants to see John.

42:41.189 --> 42:43.024
So do I.

42:43.058 --> 42:45.793
He's my friend, Ben.
He's a good guy.

42:45.827 --> 42:49.997
Yeah. He is a good guy.

